        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 5:53PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Devers to near Cove to
Pearland. Movement was southeast at 5 mph to nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pasadena, Pearland, Baytown, eastern Missouri City, northwestern
Friendswood, La Porte, Deer Park, South Houston, Bellaire, West
University Place, northern Seabrook, Galena Park, Jacinto City,
Webster, southeastern Liberty, northern Manvel, Beach City,
Cloverleaf, Fresno, and South Belt / Ellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
